content:
The fourth step in decision optimization is to add an optional filter to control which records use the optimization results. Use a filter to target a set of records to optimize recommendations. If you donâ€™t add a filter, optimized recommendations are generated for all records in the associated Salesforce object.

To create a filter that specifies which records to optimize:

Select Use Condition and configure your filter logic.
Configure your filter logic.
Select a field from the Salesforce object.
Select a logical operator.
Enter a value.
Optionally, add another condition. You can use up to 5 filters.
Click Next.
title: Filtering Records in Decision Optimization
